- GPU (Graphics Processing Unit): Similar to the muscles and organs, as it handles complex visual tasks and helps run programs smoothly.
- BIOS (Basic Input/Output System): Similar to the brain, as it controls and regulates various functions of the system.

Again, I would like to emphasize that attempting to remove these components without proper training or experience can result in serious harm to both yourself and the computer. Therefore, it is not advisable to try this on your own without professional assistance.
